#   github.com/rs/zerolog                   (structured logger)
#   github.com/robfig/cron/v3               (cron expression parser for
#                                            the --schedule flag)
#
# ddns-route53 keeps a Route 53 A/AAAA record pointed at the host's
# current WAN IP on a configurable cron schedule.  Useful for home labs
# behind dynamic-IP residential ISPs.  Config is split: CLI flags (or
# env vars) set runtime knobs (schedule, log level, network interface);
# a separate YAML config file holds AWS credentials + the list of
# hosted zones and record sets to update.  WAN IP is fetched from
# multiple providers (icanhazip.com, ifconfig.me, etc.) with retry +
# backoff.  Datetime arithmetic for the schedule + log timestamps
# routes through dromara/carbon/v2.
#
# === AXIS 177 CONTINUES — modern datetime libraries (post-stdlib-time) ===
# Axis position: Go=232 continues Axis 177 (slot 2/0/0).  Canonical Go
# modern datetime library is `github.com/dromara/carbon` (formerly
# golang-module/carbon by gouguoyin, now at the dromara collective) —
# fluent date library inspired by PHP's Carbon, providing rich datetime
# parsing/formatting/arithmetic/timezone-conversion/localized-output
# for 17+ human languages.  The "Carbon for Go" answer to "stdlib time
# is too spartan for application code that needs human-friendly date
# manipulation."  Used by ddns-route53, gobackup, chai (embedded SQL),
# m3u8-downloader, apple-store-helper, goravel framework, and many Go
# applications that ship user-visible datetime strings.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=232     _bttf                 ← previous round (axis 177 OPENS, 1/0/0)
#   Go=232       ← THIS FILE           (axis 177 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=232  ← next round          (axis 177 CLOSES at triple-232, 1/1/1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_ddns-route53() {
    _arguments -s \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show context-sensitive help]' \
        '(- *)--version[print version and exit]' \
        '--config=[ddns-route53 YAML configuration file (env CONFIG)]:config file:_files -g "*.(yml|yaml|YML|YAML)"' \
        '--schedule=[CRON expression format for the update schedule (env SCHEDULE; e.g. `*/5 * * * *` for every 5 minutes)]:cron expression:' \
        '--ifname=[network interface name to use for WAN IP retrieval (env IFNAME; leave empty for default)]:interface name:' \
        '--max-retries=[number of retries on WAN IP retrieval + AWS request failure (default 3, env MAX_RETRIES)]:N:' \
        '--max-backoff-delay=[max back-off delay between retries (default 5s, env MAX_BACKOFF_DELAY)]:duration:' \
        '--log-level=[log level (default info, env LOG_LEVEL)]:level:(trace debug info warn error fatal panic)' \
        '--log-json[enable JSON logging output (env LOG_JSON)]' \
        '--log-caller[add file:line of the caller to log output (env LOG_CALLER)]' \
        '--log-nocolor[disable colorized output (env LOG_NOCOLOR)]'
}

_ddns-route53 "$@"
